(The pride of the chefs is at stake.)

760
00:25:59,303 --> 00:26:00,632
(Which team will win the Spring Meal Battle?)

761
00:26:00,633 --> 00:26:03,272
- Team Sam Kim rang the bell first.
- Yes.

762
00:26:03,273 --> 00:26:05,172
The judges will taste their food first.

763
00:26:05,173 --> 00:26:06,603
Serve your dishes.

764
00:26:06,903 --> 00:26:09,242
Right here. What should they start with?

765
00:26:09,243 --> 00:26:12,213
(A Western-Korean fusion meal with a hint of spring aroma)

766
00:26:13,583 --> 00:26:16,583
Please explain your dishes to the panel of our judges.

767
00:26:16,683 --> 00:26:20,383
For the first dish, I grilled a halibut.

768
00:26:20,723 --> 00:26:23,252
It's a grilled halibut dish, but I added potatoes...

769
00:26:23,253 --> 00:26:26,693
and mushrooms and finished with a lemon butter sauce.

770
00:26:26,893 --> 00:26:28,722
It will have a soft texture.

771
00:26:28,723 --> 00:26:30,062
After that, I recommend...

772
00:26:30,063 --> 00:26:31,432
- the sujebi.
- Sujebi.

773
00:26:31,433 --> 00:26:35,603
I topped it off with Manila clams and pen shells at the end.

774
00:26:36,533 --> 00:26:39,842
(Manila clam and pen shell sujebi)

775
00:26:39,843 --> 00:26:41,402
For the last dish, I prepared the steak.

776
00:26:41,403 --> 00:26:43,123
- It's getting cold. Let them eat.
- You...

777
00:26:43,373 --> 00:26:44,672
- You can eat...
- Hurry up.

778
00:26:44,673 --> 00:26:46,012
The steak with the sauce.

779
00:26:46,013 --> 00:26:47,283
(Can we eat now?)

780
00:26:47,443 --> 00:26:49,482
All right. Enjoy.

781
00:26:49,483 --> 00:26:50,912
Make sure to try them in order.

782
00:26:50,913 --> 00:26:53,182
- Please eat this first.
- Are there 11 pieces of steak?

783
00:26:53,183 --> 00:26:54,252
- A piece of steak for each person.
- Tear off...

784
00:26:54,253 --> 00:26:55,782
- Please follow the order.
- some fish.

785
00:26:55,783 --> 00:26:58,652
Enjoy it with potatoes and the sauce.

786
00:26:58,653 --> 00:27:00,333
Make sure to enjoy the fish and the sauce.

787
00:27:04,663 --> 00:27:06,202
Rinse your mouth while tasting it.

788
00:27:06,203 --> 00:27:07,462
(Is it good?)

789
00:27:07,463 --> 00:27:08,463
(Thumbs-up)

790
00:27:09,603 --> 00:27:10,773
(Surprised)

791
00:27:11,903 --> 00:27:14,403
Jae Hwan gave him the thumbs-up.

792
00:27:14,873 --> 00:27:15,873
(Exclaiming)

793
00:27:15,874 --> 00:27:18,412
The fish tastes like a chicken dish.

794
00:27:18,413 --> 00:27:19,483
- Right?
- Yes.

795
00:27:19,583 --> 00:27:21,459
- It's like...
- The fish has a chicken texture.

796
00:27:21,483 --> 00:27:22,953
The sauce is really good.

797
00:27:23,613 --> 00:27:24,812
They must be surprised.

798
00:27:24,813 --> 00:27:26,322
Everyone is exclaiming.

799
00:27:26,323 --> 00:27:27,699
(Exclamations coming from all directions)

800
00:27:27,723 --> 00:27:29,522
- They look like fish roe.
- There's some tartness.

801
00:27:29,523 --> 00:27:30,693
- Tartness?
- Tartness?

802
00:27:30,893 --> 00:27:32,252
- It's tart?
- Tartness?

803
00:27:32,253 --> 00:27:33,653
Are you drinking wine or something?

804
00:27:34,523 --> 00:27:36,203
Everyone is pretending to be Anh Sung Jae.

805
00:27:37,293 --> 00:27:39,363
They keep coming. Help yourselves.

806
00:27:39,863 --> 00:27:42,403
That's a satisfied look. He's glaring.

807
00:27:42,803 --> 00:27:43,932
We give that look often...

808
00:27:43,933 --> 00:27:45,453
- when the food is delicious.
- Right.

809
00:27:46,073 --> 00:27:49,473
(Tasting manila clam and pen shell sujebi)

810
00:27:50,043 --> 00:27:52,672
- They seem to enjoy it.
- Things will work out for us.

811
00:27:52,673 --> 00:27:54,112
It's a familiar taste.

812
00:27:54,113 --> 00:27:55,483
The sujebi is a little...

813
00:27:56,213 --> 00:27:58,382
(Will sujebi be an unforeseen obstacle?)

814
00:27:58,383 --> 00:28:00,683
It's Byung Jin. He grabbed it.

815
00:28:01,283 --> 00:28:02,323
Until the end.

816
00:28:05,523 --> 00:28:06,722
I want to taste some.

817
00:28:06,723 --> 00:28:08,263
I want to taste the halibut too.

818
00:28:08,793 --> 00:28:10,233
They finished everything completely.

819
00:28:10,493 --> 00:28:12,533
They ate everything.

820
00:28:13,463 --> 00:28:14,563
They might throw up.

821
00:28:16,373 --> 00:28:19,643
Please bring the next dishes.

822
00:28:19,843 --> 00:28:21,172
- Hey. Be careful.
- That should be eaten hot...

823
00:28:21,173 --> 00:28:22,503
to enjoy the best taste.

824
00:28:23,743 --> 00:28:25,312
(An exquisite spring created from the fingertips...)

825
00:28:25,313 --> 00:28:26,883
(of a Japanese cuisine master)

826
00:28:28,183 --> 00:28:30,353
(Warming up the braised silver pomfret and radish)

827
00:28:31,553 --> 00:28:33,823
What? You can't make it warm.

828
00:28:34,383 --> 00:28:36,083
(Embarrassed)

829
00:28:38,293 --> 00:28:42,293
(Including warm braised silver pomfret and radish)

830
00:28:42,793 --> 00:28:43,892
The dishes are here.

831
00:28:43,893 --> 00:28:46,732
Three dishes are prepared.

832
00:28:46,733 --> 00:28:50,603
The first dish is braised silver pomfret in soy sauce.

833
00:28:50,973 --> 00:28:53,073
Radish was cooked until soft.

834
00:28:53,573 --> 00:28:55,102
Please scoop some silver pomfret...

835
00:28:55,103 --> 00:28:57,543
and wet it with the soy sauce at the bottom.

836
00:28:57,713 --> 00:29:00,283
Enjoy it with some rice.

837
00:29:00,983 --> 00:29:05,483
The second dish is deep-fried aralia sprout and shrimp.

838
00:29:06,183 --> 00:29:08,223
The last one is the problematic webfoot octopus.

839
00:29:08,423 --> 00:29:09,853
(I ruined the deep-fried food.)

840
00:29:09,993 --> 00:29:11,823
It's nurungji soup with webfoot octopus.

841
00:29:12,023 --> 00:29:13,693
The deep-fried batter is...

842
00:29:14,563 --> 00:29:18,162
coated in chili sauce.

843
00:29:18,163 --> 00:29:19,523
I tried it, and it was incredible.

844
00:29:20,833 --> 00:29:21,902
Welcome.

845
00:29:21,903 --> 00:29:23,072
(Team Ho Young's food tasting starts.)

846
00:29:23,073 --> 00:29:24,703
- Thank you.
- Are you done serving?

847
00:29:26,443 --> 00:29:28,943
(Taking a bite of braised silver pomfret first)

848
00:29:29,443 --> 00:29:31,042
- How's the deep-fried food?
- It's good.

849
00:29:31,043 --> 00:29:32,543
(A truthful frown)

850
00:29:32,773 --> 00:29:34,913
- Try the braised dish. It's real.
- Okay.

851
00:29:36,013 --> 00:29:38,053
(Exclaiming)

852
00:29:38,653 --> 00:29:39,922
- It's good.
- It's very good.

853
00:29:39,923 --> 00:29:41,153
The braised fish is excellent.

854
00:29:41,423 --> 00:29:42,453
Goodness.

855
00:29:42,923 --> 00:29:44,052
It's delicious.

856
00:29:44,053 --> 00:29:46,169
(Everyone likes the braised silver pomfret and radish.)

857
00:29:46,193 --> 00:29:48,792
- They love the braised dish.
- They say that they like it.

858
00:29:48,793 --> 00:29:50,993
- The braised dish got compliments.
- The braised dish.

859
00:29:51,363 --> 00:29:53,062
(An enthusiastic response that exceeds expectations)

860
00:29:53,063 --> 00:29:54,763
They said, "This is it."

861
00:29:55,933 --> 00:29:57,302
(Nervous)

862
00:29:57,303 --> 00:29:58,702
- How does ginger taste so good?
- Seriously.

863
00:29:58,703 --> 00:30:00,903
- The amount of braised dish...
- Can I have some more?

864
00:30:01,243 --> 00:30:02,673
They finished the braised dish.

865
00:30:03,273 --> 00:30:04,812
The braised dish is gone.

866
00:30:04,813 --> 00:30:06,149
(Is there more braised silver pomfret and radish?)

867
00:30:06,173 --> 00:30:07,583
- Mix them.
- Hey.

868
00:30:07,813 --> 00:30:09,142
Suddenly, with flour...

869
00:30:09,143 --> 00:30:10,553
Why are you eating this again?

870
00:30:11,753 --> 00:30:13,923
(They're eating leftover food from Team Sam Kim.)

871
00:30:14,453 --> 00:30:15,623
(What?)

872
00:30:16,293 --> 00:30:19,993
Suddenly, Byung Jin Mo ate our food again.

873
00:30:20,523 --> 00:30:24,033
Sir, you can't bring food from another restaurant.

874
00:30:24,833 --> 00:30:27,503
(Why did he do that?)

875
00:30:27,933 --> 00:30:29,433
Maybe he was comparing.

876
00:30:29,733 --> 00:30:31,532
- That's possible.
- He was comparing the two.

877
00:30:31,533 --> 00:30:32,833
(Activating positive thinking)

878
00:30:33,473 --> 00:30:36,773
(Tasting the problematic chili webfoot octopus nurungji soup)

879
00:30:37,213 --> 00:30:40,183
(What feedback will it receive?)

880
00:30:40,283 --> 00:30:42,142
- The webfoot octopus isn't ruined.
- Is it good?

881
00:30:42,143 --> 00:30:43,282
Yes.

882
00:30:43,283 --> 00:30:44,982
- It's not ruined.
- No.

883
00:30:44,983 --> 00:30:45,983
It tastes like...

884
00:30:46,883 --> 00:30:48,082
- Now...
- I want to try some.

885
00:30:48,083 --> 00:30:50,553
The judges will make a choice now.

886
00:30:51,923 --> 00:30:57,233
(The moment of destiny, what will the 11 judges choose?)

887
00:30:57,333 --> 00:30:58,563
The halibut was really...

888
00:30:59,263 --> 00:31:00,362
- Was it good?
- It was good.

889
00:31:00,363 --> 00:31:02,802
Each of Chef Ho Young's three dishes was unique.

890
00:31:02,803 --> 00:31:04,703
I could enjoy three different flavors.

891
00:31:04,933 --> 00:31:08,202
The radish in braised silver pomfret was amazing.

892
00:31:08,203 --> 00:31:12,043
The steak and halibut were so good...

893
00:31:12,513 --> 00:31:13,842
that they beat everything else.

894
00:31:13,843 --> 00:31:14,942
Chef Sam Kim.

895
00:31:14,943 --> 00:31:16,083
Chef Jung Ho Young.

896
00:31:16,753 --> 00:31:18,812
(Who will be the winner of Spring Meal Battle: Flavor Versus Flavor?)

897
00:31:18,813 --> 00:31:21,053
(The voting ends.)

898
00:31:23,993 --> 00:31:25,673
All right. The colors are different today.

899
00:31:27,523 --> 00:31:29,193
- Okay.
- One for each.

900
00:31:29,863 --> 00:31:32,863
- Are the colors pink and blue?
- Yes.

901
00:31:33,133 --> 00:31:34,232
I'm so nervous.

902
00:31:34,233 --> 00:31:36,263
(The die has been cast.)

903
00:31:36,473 --> 00:31:37,803
Please check each one.

904
00:31:38,373 --> 00:31:40,972
- I'll pick each one. All right.
- Please.

905
00:31:40,973 --> 00:31:42,543
- Please.
- The first ball is...

906
00:31:43,213 --> 00:31:45,213
- Please save us.
- The first ball is...

907
00:31:45,473 --> 00:31:46,883
- Please.
- The first ball is...

908
00:31:49,343 --> 00:31:50,583
It's blue.

909
00:31:51,313 --> 00:31:52,552
There's a total of 11. I'll keep going.

910
00:31:52,553 --> 00:31:54,952
- Please.
- For now, I'll pick up to five.

911
00:31:54,953 --> 00:31:56,082
Here's the second ball.

912
00:31:56,083 --> 00:31:57,493
(What about the second ball?)

913
00:32:00,563 --> 00:32:01,923
(The second ball is pink.)

914
00:32:02,663 --> 00:32:04,062
- Okay.
- The scores are tied.

915
00:32:04,063 --> 00:32:06,833
Which team will take the lead?

916
00:32:07,763 --> 00:32:08,763
Yes!

917
00:32:08,764 --> 00:32:10,432
(Yes, it's pink.)

918
00:32:10,433 --> 00:32:12,432
- Why are you so excited?
- It's pink.

919
00:32:12,433 --> 00:32:13,902
- What's this?
- Why are you so excited?

920
00:32:13,903 --> 00:32:15,372
We don't know the result yet.

921
00:32:15,373 --> 00:32:16,512
- Not yet.
- We have a long way to go.

922
00:32:16,513 --> 00:32:18,412
- Here's the 4th ball.
- We have 8 left.

923
00:32:18,413 --> 00:32:20,043
Will the difference get bigger?

924
00:32:20,343 --> 00:32:22,043
- Please.
- It's blue.

925
00:32:22,713 --> 00:32:23,713
Okay.

926
00:32:23,714 --> 00:32:25,513
(Relieved)

927
00:32:25,883 --> 00:32:26,952
It's blue.

928
00:32:26,953 --> 00:32:28,583
- Goodness.
- It's all right.

929
00:32:28,883 --> 00:32:30,692
The scores are tied. This is quite entertaining.

930
00:32:30,693 --> 00:32:32,952
Which team will break the tie?

931
00:32:32,953 --> 00:32:33,992
(The fifth ball is...)

932
00:32:33,993 --> 00:32:34,993
(blue.)

933
00:32:34,994 --> 00:32:36,532
- It's blue. It's for Sam Kim.
- Okay.

934
00:32:36,533 --> 00:32:37,533
All right.

935
00:32:37,534 --> 00:32:40,202
It'd be dangerous if the gap gets bigger next.

936
00:32:40,203 --> 00:32:43,103
Will Sam Kim win by widening the gap?

937
00:32:43,573 --> 00:32:46,643
(Team Sam Kim wins the vote.)

938
00:32:46,973 --> 00:32:49,402
- The score is 4 to 2. Double score.
- It's 4 to 2.

939
00:32:49,403 --> 00:32:50,872
We have six balls so far.

940
00:32:50,873 --> 00:32:52,072
We have five left.

941
00:32:52,073 --> 00:32:53,382
- I'm nervous.
- The difference is two.

942
00:32:53,383 --> 00:32:55,482
If the next ball goes to Sam again...

943
00:32:55,483 --> 00:32:56,612
(If the next ball is also blue)

944
00:32:56,613 --> 00:32:57,912
The balance will shift.

945
00:32:57,913 --> 00:32:58,913
What will it be?

946
00:33:02,753 --> 00:33:05,852
(The sixth ball is blue.)

947
00:33:05,853 --> 00:33:07,062
(Team Ho Young 2: Team Sam Kim 5)

948
00:33:07,063 --> 00:33:08,293
We're almost there.

949
00:33:09,023 --> 00:33:11,363
More than half of the result is out.

950
00:33:11,463 --> 00:33:12,563
How do you feel?

951
00:33:14,903 --> 00:33:16,673
His mood fluctuates a lot.

952
00:33:16,973 --> 00:33:18,333
I hope it's pink this time.

953
00:33:18,533 --> 00:33:20,702
The rest of them must be pink in order to turn the tables.

954
00:33:20,703 --> 00:33:23,023
(All the remaining balls must be pink to turn the tables.)

955
00:33:23,173 --> 00:33:24,473
What's that green onion for?

956
00:33:24,613 --> 00:33:26,212
Will the scores tie? All right.

957
00:33:26,213 --> 00:33:28,013
(I want to hold onto something.)

958
00:33:29,113 --> 00:33:31,683
(There's no turning back for Team Ho Young.)

959
00:33:32,453 --> 00:33:33,923
(Trembling)

960
00:33:35,253 --> 00:33:36,792
(The eighth ball is...)

961
00:33:36,793 --> 00:33:37,793
(pink.)

962
00:33:39,253 --> 00:33:40,262
(Exclaiming)

963
00:33:40,263 --> 00:33:41,723
- It's pink.
- Good.

964
00:33:42,323 --> 00:33:43,532
What's the score now?

965
00:33:43,533 --> 00:33:44,792
- It's 5 to 3.
- It's 5 to 3.

966
00:33:44,793 --> 00:33:46,133
All of them must be ours.

967
00:33:46,633 --> 00:33:49,462
(Will there be a miracle?)

968
00:33:49,463 --> 00:33:50,533
Is it blue?

969
00:33:51,603 --> 00:33:53,072
(The ninth ball is...)

970
00:33:53,073 --> 00:33:55,542
(pink.)

971
00:33:55,543 --> 00:33:57,513
- What?
- Seriously?

972
00:33:57,813 --> 00:34:00,042
(Suddenly, he feels nervous.)

973
00:34:00,043 --> 00:34:01,882
We only have two left.

974
00:34:01,883 --> 00:34:04,353
We have two left. I'll take them out at the same time.

975
00:34:04,453 --> 00:34:06,613
- Which one will it be?
- Do you think that we'll win?

976
00:34:06,883 --> 00:34:07,953
I think so.

977
00:34:08,083 --> 00:34:09,283
Do you feel victory coming?

978
00:34:10,053 --> 00:34:11,093
No, I think I'll lose.

979
00:34:11,593 --> 00:34:13,093
That was a good guess.

980
00:34:13,193 --> 00:34:14,263
Goodbye.

981
00:34:14,563 --> 00:34:16,863
(The remaining 2 balls are blue.)

982
00:34:17,263 --> 00:34:19,232
(Team Ho Young 4: Team Sam Kim 7)

983
00:34:19,233 --> 00:34:20,263
We won.

984
00:34:20,963 --> 00:34:21,963
(Screaming)

985
00:34:23,733 --> 00:34:25,472
Here's the result...

986
00:34:25,473 --> 00:34:27,543
of Spring Meal Battle: Flavor Versus Flavor.

987
00:34:27,943 --> 00:34:29,343
With a score of 7 to 4,

988
00:34:29,743 --> 00:34:31,642
- Team Sam Kim won.
- Yes!

989
00:34:31,643 --> 00:34:32,773
Congratulations.

990
00:34:33,583 --> 00:34:36,083
Sam Kim, please tell us how you feel.

991
00:34:36,283 --> 00:34:37,452
You should work harder.

992
00:34:37,453 --> 00:34:40,683
I hope that you make your food less sweet.

993
00:34:42,283 --> 00:34:43,752
On "Culinary Class Wars,"

994
00:34:43,753 --> 00:34:45,353
he did worse than me.

995
00:34:46,223 --> 00:34:47,262
- He had to point that out.
- Still,

996
00:34:47,263 --> 00:34:48,863
he's a good chef.

997
00:34:49,363 --> 00:34:50,363
He's a chef...

998
00:34:50,893 --> 00:34:54,033
who's always hardworking and crazy about cooking.

999
00:34:54,203 --> 00:34:55,233
Thank you.

1000
00:34:55,333 --> 00:34:56,933
I definitely respect him.

1001
00:34:57,073 --> 00:34:58,102
He's a good cook.

1002
00:34:58,103 --> 00:35:00,073
Thank you so much for cooking.

1003
00:35:00,173 --> 00:35:01,373
The winning team will enjoy...

1004
00:35:01,403 --> 00:35:04,773
the food made by both teams tonight for dinner.

1005
00:35:05,073 --> 00:35:06,172
- Really?
- Yes.

1006
00:35:06,173 --> 00:35:07,742
We eat again? This is a gastronomic trip.

1007
00:35:07,743 --> 00:35:08,942
I want some food too.

1008
00:35:08,943 --> 00:35:10,183
To encourage them...

1009
00:35:10,453 --> 00:35:12,452
to devote themselves more to cooking,

1010
00:35:12,453 --> 00:35:15,353
we ask the losing team to be official chefs for 2 Days 1 Night.

1011
00:35:15,383 --> 00:35:17,753
If we ask them to make us ramyeon...

1012
00:35:18,523 --> 00:35:20,262
(We will make it for you.)

1013
00:35:20,263 --> 00:35:21,492
Let's move.

1014
00:35:21,493 --> 00:35:23,392
- Okay.
- Yes.

1015
00:35:23,393 --> 00:35:24,792
(The mind-blowing dinner with the two chefs is...)

1016
00:35:24,793 --> 00:35:26,632
(on our 2 Days 1 Night YouTube Channel.)

1017
00:35:26,633 --> 00:35:29,703
A gastronomic trip for one team, a fasting retreat for the other.

1018
